folder: Ave. T & Nostrand Ave., Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Ave. T, north side; between Nostrand Ave. and Haring Street, showing at the right the home of J. Stillwell from 1857-1860, and of J.S. Ryder in 1873. This house is standing to-day (1929) and is at the N.W. corner of Haring Street and Nostrand Ave. The other house No. 2941 Ave. T, was designated (1916) as at the N.E. corner of Ryder Ave., and Ave. T.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, another view.
April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, looking south from Ave. S, along Ryder Ave. The house (at left) partially seen is No. 3303 Nostrand Ave. Judge Nicholas Stillwell's house is in the background.

April 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
